Key Architecture Components (From Leak)
memory.md (External Memory Layer): The leaked code shows Claude maintains a persistent memory.md file. This acts as a semantic index or "pointer system" rather than just a simple log.
Domain-Specific Memory Files: The agent writes structured information to dedicated files (e.g., memory/project-context.md, memory/decisions.md, memory/user-preferences.md).
Grep-based Search: Claude uses local file search tools to scan the codebase for information, treating the file system as an active, queryable database to understand project structure.
Self-Healing/Persistence: The architecture enables the agent to read and rewrite these files over multiple sessions, allowing it to maintain context even after a conversation or session has been reset. 
